IFPREVERB LOOK 5
  ECHO PLAYER Try reading it.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB READ 5
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER ------------------------------------------------------
  ECHO PLAYER If a player has a weapon that needs to be changed you
  ECHO PLAYER need to take it from them and LOOK at it. It will list
  ECHO PLAYER the ARCHNUM you need to change it to, and the ITEMBIT
  ECHO PLAYER you need to set. Remember that ITEMBIT0 is the first
  ECHO PLAYER position. So ITEMBIT : 6 would be '------*' as what
  ECHO PLAYER you should change on the weapon (remember to keep OLD
  ECHO PLAYER ITEMBITs intact!!!) All the 'standard' weapons that
  ECHO PLAYER have variants using ITEMBITs also have a LOOK that
  ECHO PLAYER gives some details of what it does and how.
  ECHO PLAYER ------------------------------------------------------
  ECHO PLAYER NOTE: *IF* the item needs no item bits you can make
  ECHO PLAYER       it into the 1 lb lighter variant if it is a
  ECHO PLAYER       1-handed weapon. The lighter versions can be 
  ECHO PLAYER       seen via @GLOSS <weapon name> or TAP SIGN. :)
  ECHO PLAYER ------------------------------------------------------
ENDIF
